    "shortDesc": "Psoriasis, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Psoriasis, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Psoriasis is a chronic skin condition where your immune system causes skin cells to grow too quickly, leading to thick, red, scaly patches that often itch or burn. The exact cause isn't fully understood, but it involves a combination of genetic factors and triggers like stress, infections, or certain medications. When doctors use 'unspecified,' it means the patient has psoriasis but the specific type or pattern hasn't been clearly identified or documented.",
